<P>THE LIFE OF DAVID HUME, <ABBR>E&s;q</ABBR> The PHILOSOPHER AND HISTORIAN, WRITTEN BY HIMSELF. TO WHICH ARE ADDED, THE TRAVELS of a PHILOSOPHER, CONTAINING Ob&s;ervations on the Manners and Arts of various Nations, in Africa and A&s;ia.</P>
<P>From the FRENCH of M. le POIVRE, Late Envoy to the King of Cochin-China, and now Intendant of the I&s;les of Bourbon and Mauritius.</P>
<P>PHILADELPHIA: Printed and Sold by ROBERT BELL, next Door to St. Paul's Church, in Third-Street. M,DCC,LXXVIII.</P>
</DIV1>
</FRONT>
